Kaizer Chiefs and Bafana Bafana goalkeeper Itumeleng Khune has been appointed to captain the national team in two international friendlies against Guinea-Bissau and Angola.Bidvest Wits defender Thulani Hlatshwayo, SuperSport United captain Dean Furman and Mamelodi Sundowns captain Hlompho Kekana have been appointed as vice captains.Bafana Bafana face Guinea-Bissau at Moses Mabhida Stadium in Durban on Saturday, 25 March at 3pm.Their next fixture will be against Angola three days later, on Tuesday, at Buffalo City Stadium in East London.-Ntsako Mashaba